_______________________________________________________________________________
SAILS PROJECT DATABASE ENDPOINTS

There must be a database created with the needed tables

npm install sails-mysql --save (make sure mysql is installed)

sails new sails-student-api

cd sails-student-api

CONFIG:

config/cors.js
    Uncomment "allRoutes" and change it from false to true
    Uncomment "origin: '*'"

config/models.js
    Uncomment "connection" and set the name to "someMysqlServer" (this is arbitrary)
    Add the following:
        // default launch to safe and not alter
        migrate: 'safe',
        // this means 'pay attention to my schema' to disallow invalid data
        schema: true,
        // prevent creation of these two timestamps
        autoCreatedAt: false,
        autoUpdatedAt: false

config/connections.js
    This is for remote databases. The local.js sets up the connection for local databases.
    The default that sails.js uses is sqlLITE


THIS IS ON THE API ONLY AND NOT ON THE FRONTEND!!!!!
config/local.js
    Add the following (at the bottom of the file):

        // environment: process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development'
        connections: {
            someMysqlServer: {
            adapter: 'sails-mysql',
            host: '127.0.0.1',
            user: 'root', //optional
            password: 'C0ldiron', //optional
            database: 'student_api' //optional
            }
        }

config/blueprints.js
    Set "defaultLimit:" to "-1" to override sails.js sending only 30 records at a time.
    This will return all available records

DEFINE ENDPOINT MODEL ATTRIBUTES:
sails generate api [name-of-endpoint]
cd api/controllers
edit [name-of-endpoint].js
cd api/models
edit [name-of-endpoint].js
